About Myself

Welcome to Teckmon{STER}!

This is my portfolio where I am sharing some interested projects I am currently working on at leisure. {STER} refers to SCIENCE, TECHNOLOGY, ENGINEERING, and RESEARCH.

Data analytics is inherently interdisciplinary with a vast array of applications. Modern technology generates enormous amounts of data, yet the ability to analyze and apply this data well and with relevance is still lacking. There are a lot of topics that I am passionate and curious to learn more about such as healthcare, fitness, nutrition, national geographics, logistics, and travel.

I hope that by working on these projects and it will prepare me with the skills necessary to be ready fields heavily involved with data analytics and machine learning and bring the design into real world use.

Since graduating from Georgia Tech in 2013, I have worked in both an academic endowment investment setting and in the corporate insurance industry. In these roles, I have built an extensive understanding of data gathering, processing, automation, and database development. With this background, I hope to expand my ability to analyze and apply data.

Beside data analytics, I weightlift, practice yoga, meditate, back country backpack, and build website with Jekyll.
